text.div: **test From Nwas111 - No Action Required - Please Disregard Test

<content styleCode="bold">Pathways Disposition: Dx10</content> <br/> <content>Must Contact A Local Service For A Non-urgent Appointment User comment - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Consultation Summary:</content> <br/> <content>Illness - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>Warm to touch</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Pathways Assessment:</content> <br/> <content>An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 2 hours.</content> <br/> <content>An illness or health problem was the main problem.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>The individual was not fighting for breath.</content> <br/> <content>The main reason for the assessment was not an allergic reaction, heart attack, chest/upper back pain, probable stroke, recent fit/seizure or suicide attempt.</content> <br/> <content>The main reason for contact was not new confusion, declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia, or ICD shock.</content> <br/> <content>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.</content> <br/> <content>Pathway selected - Difficulty Passing Urine</content> <br/> <content>The individual was able to carry out most or all normal activities.</content> <br/> <content>There was no new loss of bowel control or leg movement and no saddle or lower limb paraesthesia.</content> <br/> <content>There was no inability to pass urine over the last 12 hours.</content> <br/> <content>There was no new or worsening confusion.</content> <br/> <content>Breathing harder or faster when doing nothing was not described.</content> <br/> <content>There was no spinal pain.</content> <br/> <content>The pain was not getting worse.</content> <br/> <content>There was no fever at the time of assessment or within the previous 12 hours.</content> <br/> <content>The individual had not experienced a back injury within the previous 4 weeks.</content> <br/> <content>Medication type or dosage had not changed within the previous 2 weeks.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - 'Urgent Treatment Centre - Same Day Health Centre - Fleetwood'</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Advice Given:</content> <br/> <content>Unless advised not to, paracetamol may be used to relieve pain or fever. Follow the instructions in the pack. If in doubt ask a pharmacist.</content> <br/> <br/>
